The implementation of the recommendations therein for the necessary
                        reorganization of the NATO military
                        structure to provide for the integrated force and its supreme commander;

Recognizing that the ultimate success of such a force
lies in its sound initiation and that, for this reason, the selection of the
first supreme commander is a question of the utmost importance;

Reposing the greatest faith in General of the Army
Dwight D. Eisenhower as a commander of incomparable prestige, proven
ability, and the highest order of leadership;
